The paper discusses a technique for selecting appropriate abstract domains for software model checking based on the usage of program variables. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE), specifically program analysis and verification (cs.PL), logic in computer science (cs.LO), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as model checking is a common technique used in AI.
